.TH "SIMPLE SHELL" "1" "NOVEMBER 2018" "SIMPLE SHELL" "Simple Shell User Manual"
.SH NAME
.B hsh
- simple shell
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B
custom command line interpreter built as a project for Holberton School

command [options] [file]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple shell
is a custom version of a command language interpreter that executes
commands read from the standard input or from a file.
.SH INVOCATION
.IP
.PP
.nf
hsh can be invoked in interactive or non-interactive mode

In interactive mode, you can type commands from the keyboard:
./hsh
/bin/ls


In non-interactive mode, you can pipe commands into the program using echo
or cat:

Non-interactive:
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.SH BUILTIN COMMANDS
.B env

prints the environment
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.PP
.nf

To execute the shell:

./hsh

You can use the same syntax for running commands in other shells:

<command> <flags or options> <argument 1> <argument 2> ...

In non-interactive mode:

<command> | ./hsh

.SH EXAMPLE
.IP
.PP
.NF

Interactive mode:

/bin/ls

Non-interactive mode:

echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

.IP

.SH RETURN

The program returns 0 for success.

.SH BUGS
Memory leaks and exit does not work

.SH AUTHOR
Michael Klein and Wendy Leung

.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR sh (1),
.BR bash (1)
